Dear Engineer,


Please allow me to ask my question in Chinese.


Recently, when using Apache's forwarding feature, there has been internal disagreement about the

MaxConnectionsPerChild parameter in prefork mode.


During peak hours, each server has around 1000 child processes.

MaxConnectionsPerChild is currently set to 0. In order to periodically resolve the DNS of the access target,

we plan to adjust MaxConnectionsPerChild so that each child process

restarts approximately once every half day.


My question is: after setting this parameter, is it possible that all 1000 processes reach the configured

connection count at the same time and terminate simultaneously, causing a service interruption?


Current server settings: maxsparechild = 20, minsparchild = 10.

If MaxConnectionsPerChild is set, should these two values also be adjusted synchronously

(to prevent all child processes from restarting at the same time during peak hours)?


If there is insufficient information, please let me know.

My phone number is below; you are welcome to call.

I can communicate in Chinese or Japanese.

I am also able to respond in Japanese.


Sorry to bother you during your busy schedule.

Best wishes for your work.


